<h1 style="margin-top: 3rem;">Derivation of Mass, Enthalpy, and Energy Balance of Heat Exchanger System</h1>

<p style="text-align:center;">
  <img src="/fa25-portfolio-kam528-ai/assets/images/Heat_port_Equations.png"
       alt="Temperature measurement points"
       style="max-width: 400px; width: 100%; border-radius: 8px;">
</p>
<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #555; text-align: center; margin-top: 0.75rem;">
  The analysis assumes steady-state operation, incompressible fluid behavior,
  negligible changes in kinetic and potential energy, no work done within the system,
  a specific heat capacity of water of 4.184&nbsp;kJ/kg·K, and an ambient reference
  temperature of 25&nbsp;°C.
</p>

<h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Thermodynamics Analysis</h2>

<p style="text-align:center;">
  <img src="/fa25-portfolio-kam528-ai/assets/images/Balance.png"
       alt="Temperature measurement points"
       style="max-width: 400px; width: 100%; border-radius: 8px;">
</p>
<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #555;">
